modules.description: Provides session management operations including generating, retrieving, updating, and clearing session data with expiration control. Works with string-based keys, values, and period integers to handle time-sensitive data. Used to manage user sessions in a PostgreSQL backend with connection pooling for efficient resource handling.

Handles cookie-based session management and persistent storage for HTTP servers, using CoHTTP, Webmachine, Async, and Lwt. Operates on session identifiers, cookie headers, and backend storage structures like in-memory maps or file-based stores. Enables secure, stateful user authentication by tracking session validity across requests.

Manages session data in a PostgreSQL database using string keys and timestamp-based expiration. Supports generating, fetching, updating, and deleting sessions, with operations executed in threads to avoid blocking the main event loop. Sessions are stored in a table with a unique key and expire after a specified period. Example tasks include storing user authentication tokens and retrieving session-specific data within a defined time window.
